The establishment of a new High Criminal Court is suspended, pending a decision of the Constitutional Court.

                     

                  
  

                     
   
The Supreme Court acts as a 
second instance court when reviewing criminal cases from County courts and as a third instance court in exceptional appeals and extraordinary remedies.

                     

                  
 

                     
   
The
 State Attorney’s Office has two department, one acting as the prosecution service, and the other undertaking legal actions to protect the property of Croatia and to apply legal remedies to protect the Constitution and the law.

                     

                  
  

                     
   
