2019 report of the People’s Ombudsperson of Croatia, p. 167.

                     
In 2012, its mandate was extended (Law on the People’s Ombudsperson, NN 76/12), and in 2014 and 2015, new regional offices were opened (Law on the People’s Ombudsperson, NN 76/12) in order to cope with the increasing number of complaints (2275 resolved cases in 2013, 2013 report of the People’s Ombudsperson of Croatia, p. 5; 3632 resolved cases in 2017, 2017 report of the People’s Ombudsperson of Croatia, p. 11.).

                     

                  
 

                     
   
In 2016, 29 % of the recommendations from 2015 were implemented; in 2018, the share increased to 65 % of the recommendations from 2017, see 2018 report of the People’s Ombudsperson of Croatia, p. 6. 

                     

                  
 

                     
   
